00:46.880 --> 00:50.179
Help me.
My client is going to jail.

00:50.250 --> 00:52.241
Oh, no, she's not.

00:52.318 --> 00:53.785
I think I've got it.

00:53.853 --> 00:55.912
Really?

00:55.989 --> 00:58.480
Look up Hasson v. Conrad.

00:58.558 --> 01:00.355
Similar circumstantial
evidence...

01:00.427 --> 01:02.088
case was thrown out.

01:02.162 --> 01:04.357
Legaleagle, thank you.

01:04.431 --> 01:06.956
You are by far
the most brilliant mind

01:07.033 --> 01:08.466
in this chat room.

01:08.535 --> 01:10.298
Thank you, Lawyer-girl.

01:10.370 --> 01:14.067
I realize we have
certain anonymity here,

01:14.140 --> 01:16.973
but do you, by any chance,
have a name?

01:19.079 --> 01:20.979
It's Charlene.

01:35.361 --> 01:37.659
I missed you yesterday.

01:39.566 --> 01:41.761
How was your day?

01:41.835 --> 01:43.200
Uneventful.

01:43.269 --> 01:45.499
I exercised for an hour
in the morning,

01:45.572 --> 01:47.938
poked around in the yard
in the afternoon,

01:48.007 --> 01:51.408
and visited with a girlfriend
down the block in the evening.

01:51.478 --> 01:53.139
Sounds innocent enough.

01:53.213 --> 01:55.681
Don't let my humdrum day
fool you, now.

01:55.748 --> 01:58.512
I also have a very dark side.

02:13.900 --> 02:15.561
Well, I'm 31

02:15.635 --> 02:18.866
with long, flowing locks
and an athletic body.

02:18.938 --> 02:20.701
Peter, what do you look like?

02:25.478 --> 02:30.472
I'm... a little older...
6'2".

02:30.550 --> 02:34.077
My hair is...
it's light.

02:34.154 --> 02:36.748
Uh, it's boyishly light.

02:39.659 --> 02:43.789
And good night to you,
Lawyer-girl.

03:26.172 --> 03:28.436
Gendler.

03:32.979 --> 03:34.640
- Good morning, Mr. Sanderson.
- Hi.

03:34.714 --> 03:35.806
Morning, Peter.

03:35.882 --> 03:37.042
How are you?

03:40.186 --> 03:41.551
Gentlemen.

03:41.621 --> 03:43.953
Oh, good. Peter's here.
We can begin.

03:44.023 --> 03:46.253
Okay.
On to pressing business.

03:46.326 --> 03:47.588
Word has come to us

03:47.660 --> 03:50.629
that coffee heiress
Mrs. Virginia Arness

03:50.697 --> 03:52.892
has dismissed
her current tax lawyers.

03:52.966 --> 03:54.593
Virginia Arness.

03:54.667 --> 03:57.363
74 years old, born and raised
in Athens, Georgia.

03:57.437 --> 03:58.529
At the age of 13,

03:58.605 --> 04:00.539
she was shipped off to
boarding school in England,

04:00.607 --> 04:02.768
where she's been residing
until just recently.

04:02.842 --> 04:04.639
That was only two days ago.

04:04.711 --> 04:06.178
Impressive.

04:06.246 --> 04:07.941
Now, we've all heard

04:08.014 --> 04:11.950
that Mrs. Arness has
a penchant for thriftiness.

04:12.018 --> 04:15.283
And that she brings new meaning
to the term "conservative."

04:15.355 --> 04:17.619
It's not going to be easy.

04:17.690 --> 04:20.214
She's paranoid
and suspicious. Peter...

04:20.293 --> 04:21.521
I'm her guy.

04:21.594 --> 04:24.222
I'm single.
I'll give her nights, weekends.

04:24.297 --> 04:25.889
Aren't you getting married
on Sunday, Todd?

04:25.965 --> 04:27.728
That's flexible.

04:27.800 --> 04:30.234
And, Peter, I wouldn't
want this to interfere

04:30.303 --> 04:32.294
with your family's
Hawaiian vacation.

04:32.372 --> 04:33.805
You go on.

04:33.873 --> 04:35.500
I got it all taken care of.

04:36.776 --> 04:37.868
<i>Mahalo.</i>

04:40.146 --> 04:42.137
Well, that's very admirable
of you, Todd.

04:42.215 --> 04:45.241
I mean, your youth
definitely makes you an ass...

04:46.653 --> 04:48.382
...et to the company,

04:48.454 --> 04:50.888
especially at the annual
softball game.

04:50.957 --> 04:54.393
But to an archconservative,
74-year-old woman?

04:55.461 --> 04:58.726
What will we do is not charge
Mrs. Arness one single red cent

04:58.798 --> 05:00.163
for her estate planning.

05:01.367 --> 05:02.356
Why?

05:02.435 --> 05:04.562
Because we don't care
about that measly fee.

05:04.637 --> 05:07.197
We use it as a loss leader
to get her corporate business,

05:07.273 --> 05:11.403
the multibillion-dollar
Arness coffee conglomerate.

05:16.416 --> 05:17.576
Hmm.

05:28.761 --> 05:30.956
How may I help you, Howie?

05:31.030 --> 05:33.430
Just thought I'd congratulate
you on turning it around.

05:33.499 --> 05:35.364
Turning what around?

05:35.435 --> 05:37.096
You snaked Gendler.

05:37.170 --> 05:39.604
Please.
Gendler doesn't bother me.

05:40.873 --> 05:43.171
Oh, that's right.
He doesn't bother you.

05:43.242 --> 05:45.233
What the heck was I thinking?

05:46.446 --> 05:48.175
Listen, I thought
maybe after work

05:48.247 --> 05:49.771
you and me go tie one on,

05:49.849 --> 05:51.874
maybe check out
some of the local talent.

05:51.951 --> 05:54.010
Can't. I'm meeting
Mrs. Arness at 6:00.

05:54.087 --> 05:56.248
And by the way,
it's "You and I go tie one on,"

05:56.322 --> 05:57.584
not "You and me go."

05:57.657 --> 05:59.318
Somebody messaging you here.

05:59.392 --> 06:00.586
Who's Lawyer-girl?

06:02.395 --> 06:03.589
Nobody.

06:03.663 --> 06:06.757
Whoa. Did someone make
a blind Internet date?

06:06.833 --> 06:09.199
No. I mean, you know,
well, technically, but no.

06:09.268 --> 06:11.964
I met her
in a legal chat room.

06:12.038 --> 06:14.563
She's, uh, very classy
and smart.

06:14.640 --> 06:15.971
When do you nail her?

06:16.042 --> 06:17.600
I'm courting her tonight
at 7:00.

06:17.677 --> 06:19.838
Oh, jeez. You're courting her.
Sounds like a hot one.

06:19.912 --> 06:21.004
And this is her?

06:21.080 --> 06:22.604
Yeah, she's attractive,
isn't she?

06:22.682 --> 06:24.240
I suppose.
It's not my cup of tea.

06:24.317 --> 06:27.013
What do you...
she is universally cute.

06:27.086 --> 06:29.145
Eh, she's a little too
anemic-Iooking, Petey.

06:29.222 --> 06:31.918
I like my jello to jiggle,
if I'm not being too subtle.

06:31.991 --> 06:33.481
You're not being too subtle.

06:33.559 --> 06:36.824
All right, as long as she spins
your knobs, I'm happy for you.

06:38.231 --> 06:40.756
Have you nailed anyone
since Kate?

06:40.833 --> 06:42.664
Nail... I was
supposed to call her.

06:42.735 --> 06:45.033
Sofia, can you get my wife
on the phone?

06:45.104 --> 06:46.503
- Ex-wife.
- Ex-wife on the phone?

06:46.572 --> 06:47.596
Right away.

06:47.673 --> 06:50.198
Can't help you with this one,
pal. See you later.

06:52.512 --> 06:55.174
Peter, you cannot break
another promise to these kids.

06:55.248 --> 06:56.510
You just can't.

06:56.582 --> 06:58.345
I said I couldn't take them
to Hawaii.

06:58.418 --> 07:00.045
I didn't say
I couldn't take them.

07:00.119 --> 07:01.643
They can spend the week
with me.

07:01.721 --> 07:04.315
They are gonna be
so disappointed.

07:04.390 --> 07:05.948
I can't talk to you right now.

07:13.466 --> 07:16.526
Um... Daddy can't take you
to Hawaii.

07:16.602 --> 07:19.070
Oh, darn.

07:19.138 --> 07:20.901
He always does this.

07:25.945 --> 07:27.708
Sanderson, party of two.

07:27.780 --> 07:29.611
Oh, you're the last
to arrive.

07:29.682 --> 07:31.172
How long has she been here?

07:31.250 --> 07:32.877
Mmm, about 20 minutes.

07:32.952 --> 07:34.510
Was she trouble?

07:39.258 --> 07:40.953
Thank you.

07:41.027 --> 07:43.495
Hello.
I'm Peter Sanderson.

07:45.398 --> 07:48.697
Well, I'm glad
they didn't send a child.

07:48.768 --> 07:52.204
I told them I specifically
wanted someone my own age.

07:57.410 --> 07:59.310
What a wonderful
French bulldog.

07:59.378 --> 08:01.903
My mother had one.
They make great companions.

08:01.981 --> 08:03.949
What's her name?

08:04.016 --> 08:09.215
His name is
William Shakespeare.

08:09.288 --> 08:10.846
Well, of course.

08:12.291 --> 08:15.522
Now, I've heard about
your unfortunate escapade.

08:15.595 --> 08:17.995
I don't have escapades.

08:18.064 --> 08:20.999
Fiasco with your
previous attorney.

08:21.067 --> 08:23.331
The man was
a thieving criminal.

08:23.402 --> 08:25.666
Just because I have
a lot of money

08:25.738 --> 08:28.571
doesn't give people
the right to overcharge.

08:28.641 --> 08:31.872
I do not enjoy
being taken advantage of.

08:31.944 --> 08:34.879
Which is why our service
is free of charge.

08:34.947 --> 08:36.972
After all, you worked hard
for your money.

08:37.049 --> 08:38.482
I'm an heiress.

08:38.551 --> 08:43.318
An heiress who worked hard
to keep her money.

08:45.391 --> 08:47.222
Now, shall we get down
to business?

08:47.293 --> 08:48.419
Fine.

08:48.494 --> 08:50.792
So, now you may hand over
your proposal.

08:50.863 --> 08:52.558
I'll take it with me.

08:54.000 --> 08:55.365
Proposal?

08:55.434 --> 08:57.994
Well, I was expecting
to meet with you tomorrow.

08:58.070 --> 09:01.198
I was assured
the proposal would be ready

09:01.274 --> 09:02.468
for this afternoon.

09:02.542 --> 09:04.806
I see no point
in our meeting tomorrow.

09:04.877 --> 09:07.402
Excuse me.
Madam, I'm sorry.

09:07.480 --> 09:10.506
We have a no-dog policy
in the lounge.

09:10.583 --> 09:13.484
Unfortunately, I'm gonna have
to ask you to remove the dog.

09:13.553 --> 09:15.453
Excuse me.
I am Mrs. Arness' attorney,

09:15.521 --> 09:17.751
and because there is no sign
posted regarding dogs,

09:17.823 --> 09:20.223
that means there is
no policy toward dogs.

09:20.293 --> 09:22.386
Now, if you want to avoid
a legal situation,

09:22.461 --> 09:24.326
I would suggest
you run to the kitchen

09:24.397 --> 09:26.763
and get some tuna tartare
for William Shakespeare

09:26.832 --> 09:28.629
on the house.

09:28.701 --> 09:29.963
Yes, sir.

09:30.036 --> 09:31.663
I'm terribly sorry, ma'am.

09:41.581 --> 09:43.606
Where and when tomorrow?

09:52.491 --> 09:53.924
Hello, Mr. Sanderson.

09:53.993 --> 09:56.291
Oh, Mrs. Kline.
Always a pleasure.

09:56.362 --> 09:58.557
And when am I going to
get to babysit

09:58.631 --> 10:00.963
with your charming
little Georgey again?

10:02.468 --> 10:04.026
Oh, uh, well, uh, soon,

10:04.103 --> 10:06.936
because he just loves
coming over to your place.

10:08.240 --> 10:10.640
Uh, Mr. Sanderson?

10:10.710 --> 10:14.908
Those Latin people
who were skulking around...

10:14.981 --> 10:18.974
Oh. They were looking
at the Aruda house.

10:19.051 --> 10:20.951
Casing it?

10:21.020 --> 10:23.147
No, uh, to buy it.

10:23.222 --> 10:25.383
Oh, please.

10:25.458 --> 10:28.825
If they're in this block and not
carrying a leaf blower...

10:28.894 --> 10:30.327
Yeah.

10:30.396 --> 10:32.455
Well, I'd love to discuss this
with you further,

10:32.531 --> 10:33.998
but I'm expecting someone.

10:34.066 --> 10:35.658
Ohh.

11:41.333 --> 11:42.391
Yeah.

11:42.468 --> 11:43.730
Hey.

11:54.046 --> 11:55.513
Hi.

12:28.948 --> 12:30.438
Yeah.

13:02.348 --> 13:04.373
I hope you like cham...

13:08.721 --> 13:09.983
...poo.

13:11.056 --> 13:12.353
What's up, baby?

13:12.424 --> 13:14.654
Ooh, champagne.
I love champagne.

13:14.727 --> 13:15.716
This for me?

13:15.795 --> 13:18.320
Oh, I'm sorry. I think
you have the wrong house.

13:18.397 --> 13:20.331
It is damn good
to finally connect.

13:20.399 --> 13:22.026
Pardon me?

13:22.101 --> 13:24.501
It's me, fool... Charlene.

13:24.570 --> 13:25.969
Ooh, food.

13:26.038 --> 13:27.164
What?

13:27.239 --> 13:30.003
It's me, honey.
Your date... Lawyer-girl.

13:30.075 --> 13:31.064
You can't be.

13:31.143 --> 13:32.667
Hey, hey, hey.
Leave that alone.

13:32.745 --> 13:33.769
Well, why can't I?

13:33.846 --> 13:35.905
Because you're not a blonde.

13:35.981 --> 13:37.744
Can't get nothing past you.

13:38.918 --> 13:40.681
You must be
a bomb-ass lawyer.

13:40.753 --> 13:43.051
Oh, look at all
of these pretty candles...

13:43.122 --> 13:45.955
all romantic and shit.

13:46.025 --> 13:49.119
Somebody was planning
on getting some booty tonight.

13:49.195 --> 13:51.163
Hey! Leave that alone.
There are settings.

13:51.230 --> 13:54.393
And you can't be Charlene,
because Charlene is more of...

13:54.466 --> 13:55.558
Skinny white broad?

13:55.634 --> 13:56.566
Yeah.

13:56.635 --> 13:58.728
You know, I get that a lot.

13:58.804 --> 14:00.897
But that's your fault
you're thinking that, bro.

14:00.973 --> 14:03.737
You must have not have took
a good look at that picture.

14:03.809 --> 14:05.777
I have looked
at that picture a lot,

14:05.845 --> 14:07.608
and trust me,
you are not in it.

14:07.680 --> 14:09.272
Mm-hmm.

14:18.557 --> 14:20.752
Move, move, move.
Let me do it.

14:20.826 --> 14:22.453
See?

14:25.564 --> 14:26.622
There I am.

14:27.700 --> 14:29.725
Sorry you got it
twisted, dog.

14:29.802 --> 14:32.100
I don't get a lot of
photo ops where I been.

14:33.973 --> 14:35.600
Where exactly have you been?

14:35.674 --> 14:38.768
I got a rumble in the jungle.
We still having dinner or what?

14:38.844 --> 14:40.334
I asked you a question.

14:40.412 --> 14:41.538
Rolex.

14:41.614 --> 14:42.774
Rolex?

14:42.848 --> 14:45.009
I did time, baby,
but I ain't do the crime.

14:45.084 --> 14:46.813
You're a convict?

14:46.886 --> 14:48.012
Bump that.

14:48.087 --> 14:49.952
Shoot,
Roscoe cracked that door.

14:50.022 --> 14:51.956
I kicked it off the heezy
and bounced.

14:52.024 --> 14:53.116
For real, though.

14:54.126 --> 14:56.253
What did you just say?

14:56.328 --> 14:58.262
What, don't you hear good?

14:59.665 --> 15:00.757
All right.

15:00.833 --> 15:03.358
Let's see.
How can I put this?

15:03.435 --> 15:06.302
I was recently liberated
from a correctional facility...

15:06.372 --> 15:07.703
All right. I get it.

15:07.773 --> 15:10.537
You're in the big house, and
you get someone to type for you,

15:10.609 --> 15:13.305
and you get on the Internet,
and you misrepresent yourself.

15:13.379 --> 15:14.607
It happens, and I'm a sucker,

15:14.680 --> 15:16.773
but now you have to go,
because this is over.

15:16.849 --> 15:18.339
Unh-unh. No, no, no.

15:18.417 --> 15:20.385
Biscuit,
you misrepresented yourself.

15:20.452 --> 15:22.283
Boyishly light... please.

15:22.354 --> 15:23.321
Gray.

15:23.389 --> 15:25.789
You said you was
a criminal lawyer.

15:25.858 --> 15:26.916
I pulled your file.

15:26.992 --> 15:29.187
You're just some sorry-ass
tax attorney.

15:29.261 --> 15:31.195
A tax lawyer is
a criminal lawyer.

15:31.263 --> 15:33.288
Oh, yeah?

15:33.365 --> 15:35.765
Well, good,
'cause that's why I'm here.

15:35.834 --> 15:37.267
Well, do tell.

15:37.336 --> 15:40.328
Well,
I want to reopen my case.

15:40.406 --> 15:44.706
And what did you do, smoke
some homies on a drive-by?

15:45.711 --> 15:47.542
Smoke? Homies?

15:47.613 --> 15:49.672
Well, you a regular
gangster, huh?

15:50.649 --> 15:54.176
No, man. I was in for armed
robbery, but I didn't do it.

15:54.253 --> 15:55.345
Yeah, nobody did it.

15:55.421 --> 15:57.218
I can't be having
this conversation

15:57.289 --> 15:58.449
because you're a criminal-type.

15:58.524 --> 16:00.458
If I was a criminal,
I would have shanked you

16:00.526 --> 16:01.959
when I had
that knife in my hand.

16:02.027 --> 16:04.359
