we could discuss your case.

19:44.016 --> 19:45.540
Ahh!

19:45.617 --> 19:47.551
What up, dog?
Where 'em bagels at?

19:47.619 --> 19:50.179
Hey, guess what, girlfriend?
Your game is up.

19:50.255 --> 19:51.847
Because I burned
all those e-mails,

19:51.924 --> 19:54.449
including the second set hidden
in the lining of your coat.

19:54.526 --> 19:56.721
And I deleted everything
off my computer.

19:56.795 --> 19:59.787
So I never met you,
and you never met me.

19:59.865 --> 20:03.232
Don't even try, girlfriend,
because it's locked.

20:03.302 --> 20:07.762
And now I am going to go
get my kids,

20:07.839 --> 20:09.272
as in innocent young persons

20:09.341 --> 20:11.309
who will never even know
you were here.

20:11.376 --> 20:12.741
So now just go.

20:12.811 --> 20:15.211
Go, go, go, go,
go, go, go, go!

20:15.280 --> 20:16.838
And locky locky!

20:16.915 --> 20:17.939
So ta-ta.

20:18.016 --> 20:20.109
And watch out.
The gate closes automatically.

20:20.185 --> 20:21.209
Well, what about my stuff?

20:21.286 --> 20:23.083
Oh, it's right there
on the street.

20:23.155 --> 20:24.782
You put my stuff
on the trash?

20:24.856 --> 20:26.824
Oh. Well, you know what?

20:26.892 --> 20:28.416
I wish you well.
I really do.

20:28.493 --> 20:30.688
And you know what?
I had a great, great time.

20:30.762 --> 20:31.820
It was really fun.

20:31.897 --> 20:33.194
So, oh, well.

20:33.265 --> 20:35.233
I guess I'll just see you
in my next life.

20:35.300 --> 20:37.325
Heh heh heh heh. Bye!

20:39.671 --> 20:42.162
Ha ha. I'll see you
when you get home.

20:47.980 --> 20:49.777
So I said to him,

20:49.848 --> 20:52.180
"Just 'cause you whisked me
to Paris on your private jet

20:52.251 --> 20:54.378
doesn't mean
I'm gonna sleep with you."

20:54.453 --> 20:56.284
What does he think I am?
A hooker?

20:56.355 --> 20:59.950
Can Aunt Ashley
edit herself, please?

21:00.025 --> 21:02.220
You stayed in
the same room with him.

21:02.294 --> 21:03.386
What did you expect?

21:03.462 --> 21:05.828
Hello. It was a suite...
plenty of floor space.

21:05.897 --> 21:08.024
Sweetiepie, have a wonderful
time. I love you.

21:08.100 --> 21:10.796
Please be good to your brother
and help him with his reading.

21:10.869 --> 21:12.166
- I will.
- Thank you.

21:12.237 --> 21:15.070
Is he still having problems?

21:15.140 --> 21:18.075
Oh, he struggles every day,
but he's improving.

21:18.143 --> 21:20.407
Dad's here.

21:20.479 --> 21:22.674
Thank you, sweetiepie.

21:22.748 --> 21:24.215
Don't worry, sweetie.

21:24.283 --> 21:26.877
Daddy's stupid, too,
and he became a lawyer.

21:26.952 --> 21:27.884
Ashley!

21:27.953 --> 21:29.215
I'm not stupid.

21:29.288 --> 21:31.051
- That's right.
- No, no, no. Of course not.

21:31.123 --> 21:32.181
Hey, Dad's here.

21:32.257 --> 21:34.248
Speak of the dummy.

21:34.326 --> 21:36.351
Hey, how's my little girl
doin', huh?

21:36.428 --> 21:37.656
Hi, Dad.

21:37.729 --> 21:39.162
Hey, how's it goin', big guy?

21:39.231 --> 21:40.698
Ahhh, here you go.

21:41.566 --> 21:43.056
Hi, Kate.

21:44.236 --> 21:45.168
Hi.

21:45.237 --> 21:47.899
Oh, Ashley, I didn't realize
you were gonna be here.

21:47.973 --> 21:49.235
What a pleasant surprise.

21:49.308 --> 21:52.072
Peter,
you're almost aging well.

21:52.144 --> 21:55.272
Okay, I thought we'd go down
to the club and take a swim.

21:55.347 --> 21:57.713
Ooh, that sounds
much more fun than Maui.

21:57.783 --> 21:59.910
You know, Ashley,
not all of us earn our living

21:59.985 --> 22:02.112
by milking rich geriatrics
out of their money.

22:02.187 --> 22:03.916
Some of us have to work
for a living.

22:03.989 --> 22:07.083
You sound much more intelligent
with your mouth shut.

22:07.159 --> 22:08.854
Let's not start this.
I don't have time.

22:08.927 --> 22:10.588
Kids, go get your stuff.

22:10.662 --> 22:11.856
All right, fine.

22:11.930 --> 22:13.488
But I warned you

22:13.565 --> 22:16.898
about marrying the first
jerk-off you met out of college.

22:16.968 --> 22:18.959
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have a date.

22:19.037 --> 22:20.971
<i>Don't</i> be good.

22:21.973 --> 22:24.407
What morgue did you find
this one at?

22:24.476 --> 22:26.569
Stop being so childish.

22:31.450 --> 22:32.974
Hey.

22:33.985 --> 22:35.919
Wow.
You look beautiful.

22:35.987 --> 22:37.079
Thank you.

22:37.155 --> 22:39.146
Mmm.

22:39.224 --> 22:41.249
Uh, hi.

22:41.326 --> 22:43.317
Uh, Peter, this is Glen.

22:44.396 --> 22:45.454
Hey.

22:45.530 --> 22:47.828
Hey, Mr. Sanderson.
Nice to see you.

22:47.899 --> 22:49.230
Yeah, nice to meet you.

22:49.301 --> 22:52.862
Uh, what do you say
we get this road on the show?

22:52.938 --> 22:53.996
Okay.

22:55.173 --> 22:56.265
I will meet you outside.

22:56.341 --> 22:57.672
Okay.

22:57.743 --> 22:58.675
Road on the show.

22:58.744 --> 23:00.507
Just don't.

23:00.579 --> 23:01.944
How old is he?

23:02.013 --> 23:03.310
Younger.

23:03.382 --> 23:04.906
- What does he do?
- Golf instructor.

23:04.983 --> 23:06.473
- How do you know that?
- What?

23:06.551 --> 23:08.109
Well, you think
you know somebody,

23:08.186 --> 23:10.654
and then one day you wake up
in Thailand missing a kidney.

23:10.722 --> 23:14.123
He could have made up
this whole golf identity.

23:14.192 --> 23:16.752
He caddied for you
when he was 14.

23:17.829 --> 23:19.990
That's little Glenny?

23:21.400 --> 23:22.958
Does that bother you?

23:23.034 --> 23:24.126
Not at all.

23:24.202 --> 23:26.932
Go have fun
on your statutory weekend.

23:30.942 --> 23:33.740
This does too bother you.
I know you.

23:34.913 --> 23:36.505
Do you want to talk
about it?

23:36.581 --> 23:38.549
Well, it just looks
a little silly.

23:38.617 --> 23:40.551
Hang on.

23:40.619 --> 23:41.711
Hello?

23:41.787 --> 23:44.779
Some things never change.

23:44.856 --> 23:47.120
I can't talk right now.

23:47.192 --> 23:49.251
Well, put him on.

23:49.327 --> 23:50.624
Hi.

23:50.695 --> 23:53.289
You promised us
you'd take us snorkeling.

23:53.365 --> 23:55.094
Things come up.
That's life.

23:55.167 --> 23:57.294
I know.
I'm really, really sorry.

23:57.369 --> 24:00.304
But now it's over. It's new.
We're gonna have a lot of fun.

24:00.372 --> 24:03.102
Now, what's new?
What's new with you?

24:03.175 --> 24:07.305
Well, I got the female lead
in the school play "Oklahoma!"

24:08.313 --> 24:10.338
Hey, that's great.
Congratulations.

24:10.415 --> 24:12.383
And how 'bout you, big guy?
How's school?

24:12.451 --> 24:13.884
I don't like school.

24:13.952 --> 24:15.283
Well, nobody likes school,

24:15.353 --> 24:17.753
but there must be something
you like about it.

24:17.823 --> 24:20.121
He got into a fight
the other day.

24:20.192 --> 24:22.524
Why?
Why'd you get in a fight?

24:22.594 --> 24:26.792
Some kids called me a baby
'cause of the way I read.

24:26.865 --> 24:29.800
Some of the greatest minds of
all time had trouble learning,

24:29.868 --> 24:34.601
like Edgar Allan Poe
and Albert Einstein

24:34.673 --> 24:36.197
and, uh, Ozzy Osbourne.

24:37.409 --> 24:38.774
Ozzy rules.

24:38.844 --> 24:40.744
Ozzy rules. Okay.

24:44.449 --> 24:46.940
Dad, what's goin' on?

24:47.018 --> 24:48.952
You two wait here.
I'll be right back.

24:53.058 --> 24:54.025
Hey!

24:54.092 --> 24:56.458
Whoa, whoa. Where you think
you're goin', milk?

24:56.528 --> 24:58.359
This here's
a charitable event.

24:58.430 --> 25:01.092
You wants to get in,
you gots to make a donation.

25:01.166 --> 25:03.532
Trust me, it is
off the hook in there.

25:03.602 --> 25:05.194
Off the what?
I live here.

25:06.438 --> 25:08.702
I don't care
if you're Halle Berry, man.

25:08.773 --> 25:10.638
No donation, no entry.

25:10.709 --> 25:13.371
How 'bout
if I call the police?

25:16.681 --> 25:17.875
Have a nice time.

25:35.233 --> 25:36.325
Oh, yeah.

25:36.401 --> 25:38.096
Yeah, baby, show me.

25:38.169 --> 25:40.797
Hey! What the hell
is going on here?

25:40.872 --> 25:42.669
Oh, yo, P., it's cool.

25:42.741 --> 25:44.231
See, I hit up my homegirl

25:44.309 --> 25:46.675
'cause I had to get my hair
done, as we both know.

25:46.745 --> 25:49.873
And then she called a friend.
They holler to other friends.

25:49.948 --> 25:52.246
Before you know it,
we got us a house par-ty.

25:53.718 --> 25:56.084
I want everyone
out of here now!

25:56.154 --> 25:58.486
People!

25:58.557 --> 26:00.320
People!

26:00.392 --> 26:02.917
Loosen your panties, Grandma.

26:02.994 --> 26:05.827
Look, you lock me out,
no money, no place to go.

26:05.897 --> 26:08.661
I mean, a girl got to get
her cheese on.

26:08.733 --> 26:10.530
Seven.

26:10.602 --> 26:11.830
This is insane!

26:11.903 --> 26:13.962
My boss' sister lives
across the street.

26:14.039 --> 26:16.132
I can't have all these peop...

26:18.043 --> 26:18.873
Hey!

26:18.944 --> 26:21.003
Give me a hard seven, baby.

26:21.079 --> 26:22.376
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

26:22.447 --> 26:24.745
She doesn't even have
her driver's permit.

26:24.816 --> 26:25.748
Dad.

26:25.817 --> 26:27.114
Do not go...

26:27.185 --> 26:28.482
Roll! Uh!

26:28.553 --> 26:30.020
Come on.

26:30.088 --> 26:31.385
Don't inhale.

26:31.456 --> 26:34.892
All right, now. Go on
and toss them bones, lil' man.

26:35.727 --> 26:36.887
Hey! Give me...

26:36.962 --> 26:38.122
I'm on a roll, Dad.

26:39.264 --> 26:41.494
Get out.

26:41.566 --> 26:45.468
I want you and your dogs
to go back to the pound now.

26:45.537 --> 26:46.868
What?

26:50.375 --> 26:51.535
Well, it was the dogs?

26:51.610 --> 26:53.544
Because she said dogs,
and then I said dogs,

26:53.612 --> 26:55.910
so I assumed
that would be okay.

26:55.981 --> 26:57.209
Huh?

27:05.824 --> 27:07.519
Whoo!

27:10.629 --> 27:12.187
Tsk.

27:13.632 --> 27:15.600
Bye, Tamika.
Y'all be good, now.

27:15.667 --> 27:16.827
Bye.

27:18.269 --> 27:20.260
Hey, hey.
Y'all got to go.

27:20.338 --> 27:22.272
- A'ight.
- That's a'ight.

27:25.076 --> 27:26.543
Hey, baby, gonna go.

27:26.611 --> 27:29.079
Oh, bye, Bear.
Thank you so much.

27:29.147 --> 27:31.513
Party's over.
Okay. Thanks for coming.

27:31.583 --> 27:33.210
But that's it. It's over.

27:33.284 --> 27:35.684
If I see Widow around,
I'm gonna tell him you're out.

27:35.754 --> 27:37.244
You know
he wants to know that.

27:37.322 --> 27:39.187
I don't know about that.
I'll see you.

27:39.257 --> 27:40.724
- Okay. Bye, baby.
- Bye-bye.

27:42.427 --> 27:43.860
It's like this.

27:43.928 --> 27:44.952
Hey.

27:45.030 --> 27:46.520
- How you doin', neighbor?
- What's up?

27:51.002 --> 27:52.902
What are you still doing here?

27:52.971 --> 27:55.201
- What was all that, Dad?
- Dad, who's this?

27:55.273 --> 27:56.365
This is no one.

27:56.441 --> 27:57.840
Tsk! What's up, lil' Romeo?

27:57.909 --> 27:59.638
My name is Charlene.
What's your name?

27:59.711 --> 28:00.473
I'm Georgey.

28:00.545 --> 28:02.570
You cannot meet
a nonexistent person.

28:02.647 --> 28:04.877
Can Charlene come to the club?

28:04.949 --> 28:06.416
Club? What club?

28:06.484 --> 28:08.384
We're not going to a club,
remember?

28:08.453 --> 28:10.887
We're going to Hawaii,
remember?

28:10.955 --> 28:12.946
Okay, you know the routine.
Outski!

28:13.024 --> 28:14.924
- Out! Let's go.
- Come on, man!

28:14.993 --> 28:16.790
Sarah, get the door.
Come on. Out.

28:16.861 --> 28:18.385
Out, out, out!

28:19.798 --> 28:21.789
- Wait!
- What?

28:21.866 --> 28:23.197
Give me my money, lil' boy.

28:23.268 --> 28:24.826
That money should go
to charity!

28:24.903 --> 28:25.961
Ohh!

28:29.974 --> 28:31.305
What did...

28:31.376 --> 28:32.673
Hey, I live here.

28:32.744 --> 28:34.177
Yeah!

28:36.314 --> 28:37.303
What?

28:43.254 --> 28:44.482
Okay, you guys.

28:44.556 --> 28:48.492
You know, you order hot dogs,
and you splash and frolic

28:48.560 --> 28:51.051
and just put everything on
my account and just have fun.

28:51.129 --> 28:52.756
Didn't you bring
your bathing suit?

28:52.831 --> 28:55.425
Oh, no.
I'm having tea with a client.

28:55.500 --> 28:57.627
But I will be right back.

28:57.702 --> 28:59.431
Whatever you say.

28:59.504 --> 29:01.404
Want to go swimming?

29:01.473 --> 29:02.462
With you?

29:02.540 --> 29:03.802
Forget you.

29:03.875 --> 29:04.807
Ow!

29:04.876 --> 29:06.343
How's it looking?

29:06.411 --> 29:08.402
Well, I was up all night
proofing.

29:08.480 --> 29:10.107
It's absolutely brilliant.

29:10.181 --> 29:12.911
And you've got the cleanest
background check I've ever seen.

29:12.984 --> 29:15.475
That background check
cost me a lot of fun in my life.

29:15.553 --> 29:17.953
I don't know, honey.

29:18.022 --> 29:19.887
Don't say anything.
She could hear you.

29:19.958 --> 29:21.016
What's crackin', ma?

29:21.092 --> 29:23.026
I'm lookin'
for the Sanderson table.

29:23.094 --> 29:24.561
We old college buddies.

29:24.629 --> 29:27.223
O-O-Okay.
He's i-in the dining room.

29:27.298 --> 29:28.287
I-I'll show you.

29:28.366 --> 29:29.355
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

29:29.434 --> 29:31.698
I tell you what...
I'll surprise him.

29:35.240 --> 29:37.572
No, you're in great shape.
I'm gonna take off.

29:37.642 --> 29:40.076
All right, you're right.
Nothing could go wrong.

29:40.145 --> 29:42.613
I've done this a million times
with important clients,

29:42.680 --> 29:43.772
so I'm fine.

29:43.848 --> 29:45.110
- Shazam.
- What?

29:47.185 --> 29:48.174
Oh, no.

29:50.054 --> 29:53.421
Oh, swing it,
you cocoa goddess.

29:53.491 --> 29:56.426
Cocoa Goddess? That's the rude
shock I was telling you about.

29:56.494 --> 29:57.825
That's Charlene?

29:58.897 --> 30:00.489
Did she see me?

30:03.401 --> 30:05.699
Okay, okay, okay, police.

30:05.770 --> 30:08.102
Uh, no.
Won't get here fast enough.

30:08.173 --> 30:09.504
Uh, security.

30:09.574 --> 30:12.042
No, she could probably
take him.

30:24.956 --> 30:26.423
Uh, money.

30:27.926 --> 30:29.450
She'll take money.

30:29.527 --> 30:32.519
Hi, hi. Here, just...
Here's whatever.

30:32.597 --> 30:35.589
And there's more where that came
from if you just leave now.

30:35.667 --> 30:38.135
No. Unh-unh, boyfriend.
We got business.

30:38.203 --> 30:39.602
Boyfriend?

30:39.671 --> 30:41.798
Oh, didn't I tell you?
We're dating now.

30:41.873 --> 30:43.135
It's some kind of street talk.

30:43.208 --> 30:44.937
It's street for
"I'm not going nowhere

30:45.009 --> 30:46.636
until you help my problem
go away."

30:46.711 --> 30:49.805
Look, Mrs. Arness,
a very important client,

30:49.881 --> 30:52.247
is due here any minute.

30:57.555 --> 30:58.647
Good afternoon.

30:58.723 --> 31:00.623
Good afternoon.
Mr. Sanderson?

31:00.692 --> 31:02.284
Oh, yes.
He's in the dining room.

31:02.360 --> 31:04.260
Thank you.

31:04.329 --> 31:06.354
Charlene, how 'bout you and I

31:06.431 --> 31:09.423
havin' a smart cocktail
down by the pool?

31:09.500 --> 31:10.762
Who is this fool?

31:10.835 --> 31:13.235
That's a good idea.
Just put it on my bill.

31:13.304 --> 31:16.000
I don't want no smart cocktail.
I need your help.

31:16.074 --> 31:17.507
Miss.

31:17.575 --> 31:18.940
Another martini.

31:19.010 --> 31:21.171
Oh, hell, no.
I know she ain't talkin' to me.

31:21.246 --> 31:22.804
Ashley,
she doesn't work here.

31:22.881 --> 31:25.076
If she isn't here to work,
then what is she here for?

31:25.149 --> 31:28.277
Oh, hells no, Miss Thing.
You best pump your brakes.

31:28.353 --> 31:29.684
She's my ex-wife's sister.

31:29.754 --> 31:31.745
I would have killed her
myself years ago.

31:31.823 --> 31:33.814
It's Mrs. Arness!

31:36.661 --> 31:39.960
Mmm. Old Iron Ass
be lookin' mean.

31:40.031 --> 31:41.464
Yes. You have to go.

31:41.532 --> 31:43.261
You like raw oysters,
Charlene?

31:45.336 --> 31:48.271
Yeah. I guess
I can hang out for a bit.

31:48.339 --> 31:50.466
They got any hot wings
around here?

31:51.109 --> 31:52.940
All right.
Whatever you want. Yes.

31:53.011 --> 31:54.535
- You give me a place to stay?
- Yes.

31:54.612 --> 31:56.637
- And you work on my case?
- Around the clock.

31:56.714 --> 31:58.113
I'll leave
when you expunge my record.

31:58.182 --> 31:59.809
Consider it expunged.

32:01.452 --> 32:03.943
All right.
I'd like a key, please.

32:08.326 --> 32:09.452
Mr. Sanderson?

32:09.527 --> 32:11.392
Mrs. Arness.

32:12.463 --> 32:14.397
Who is your associate?

32:15.466 --> 32:18.060
This is Howie Rottman,
the attorney I told you about.

32:18.136 --> 32:20.661
A great pleasure
to meet you, Mrs. Arness.

32:20.738 --> 32:21.796
I meant her.

32:21.873 --> 32:23.500
Oh.

32:23.574 --> 32:24.563
Her?

32:24.642 --> 32:25.574
Her?

32:25.643 --> 32:27.338
Her is... her...

32:27.412 --> 32:30.040
She is our... our nanny.

32:31.582 --> 32:33.106
Dad, I'm bored.

32:33.184 --> 32:35.152
Kids, how good to see you.

32:35.219 --> 32:38.279
Don't we just love
our nanny, Charlene?

32:40.258 --> 32:42.556
Uh... Y-yeah.

32:44.696 --> 32:48.325
Don't you just love being
our nanny, Charlene?

32:55.740 --> 32:57.173
Yessir.

33:00.178 --> 33:02.908
Now I'm gonna go on down
to the pool with the child'n.

33:02.981 --> 33:05.677
Maybe we make fun of the white
folks again, huh, kids?

33:05.750 --> 33:06.910
Ooh-hoo!

33:06.985 --> 33:08.782
Oh, the kids just love her.

33:08.853 --> 33:10.377
- What a sense of humor.
- Yeah.

33:10.455 --> 33:12.423
Peter, I'm going to hang
by the pool.

33:12.490 --> 33:14.458
If you need me,
that's where I'll be.

33:14.525 --> 33:16.288
Mrs. Arness.

33:16.361 --> 33:17.919
Uh, right this way,
Mrs. Arness.

33:17.996 --> 33:19.486
Come, William.

33:19.564 --> 33:20.792
You have the papers?

33:20.865 --> 33:22.298
Oh, yes, yes, I do.

33:22.367 --> 33:23.994
Strange clothes for a nanny.

33:24.068 --> 33:26.036
Well, it's a fashion to kids.

33:26.104 --> 33:28.095
- Ow!
- William, mind.

33:39.550 --> 33:42.383
Hello, Sanderson family!

33:43.855 --> 33:45.823
Georgey,
don't forget poker night!

